              <h4>What is High Blood Pressure?</h4>
              <p>The force of your blood pushing against the walls of your blood vessels is your blood pressure (BP).  Your BP reading is the measurement of this force and is given in two numbers.  The top figure (systolic pressure) is the pressure in your vessels when your heart contracts, and the lower figure (diastolic pressure) is the pressure when your heart relaxes.</p>
