              <h4>How is high blood pressure diagnosed?</h4>
              <p>You are considered to have high blood pressure if you have a BP reading of <strong>140/90 or higher on three separate occasions</strong>. 
                If you have no risk factors for hypertension, your blood pressure should be checked at least once every 2 years.  If your blood pressure is high-normal, your blood pressure should be checked more regularly, at least every 6-12 months. 
                </p>
